<br>
Some MORON did this to my group last night in Dreadlands.  He first annoyed us to add him to our group, even though we said no.  Then he pestered my druid to give him a SOW, even though I had my AFK tag on.  Then he pestered the group next to us, and I guess they relented.  <br>
<br>
Then, I think he was soloing and overpulled, and got into trouble.  We had one mob on us and were pulling fast, so mana was running low for me, only cleric for 4 tanks.  So he /y and said help a few times, and we didnt and couldnt.  <br>
<br>
Then he died, rather than being halfway smart and running, RIGHT NEXT TO us, and sure enough we got his add.  Luckily I had 4 awsome tanks and we only needed a little extra downtime .. but this moron nearly got 5 of us killed because he was inconsiderate.<br>
<br>
I see this at the druid rings, especially COMMONS all the time.  Sure, people will help if they can, but dont EVER expect them to.  And dont ever be dumb enough to stand by another group, especially one that's fighting, while you're getting ready to die.  That's just training them.  Hell, my guild's moto is to help others, but not at the expense of the people in my group. <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://home.earthlink.net/~deliveranceeci/rexsig.jpg" width="300" height="75">  - 
